            <![CDATA[
            <p>Meta Is Dying. It’s About Time.</p>

            <blockquote>
            <p>But they are, as the kids say, peak cringe. Many teenagers wouldn’t be caught dead with an AOL account, a Yahoo email address — or a Facebook profile.[…] The more users quit, and the more corroded Meta’s apps grow, the faster we can all log off and close this chapter of the social media revolution forever.</p>
            </blockquote>

            <p>👏👏👏</p>

            <p><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/08/opinion/meta-facebook-zuckerberg.html?unlocked_article_code=1.hVA.mJJm.ImZ2WhQ3Fmvw&amp;smid=url-share">Julia Angwin</a></p>

            <p>I can proudly say that I've never had a Facebook, Instagram, or WhatsApp account.</p>
